1
00:05:50,310 --> 00:05:52,467
What happened?

2
00:05:53,010 --> 00:05:58,758
Too crippled by your repentance to look me in the eye?

3
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,470
True...

4
00:06:04,330 --> 00:06:08,930
I've always been true...

5
00:06:08,930 --> 00:06:13,590
To my love for you...

6
00:06:13,590 --> 00:06:21,870
To the flimsy illusion you conjured up...

7
00:06:21,870 --> 00:06:27,997
And to myself... All my life...

8
00:06:27,997 --> 00:06:30,810
But you...

9
00:06:30,810 --> 00:06:37,849
Like every puny liar before you, you tried erasing my truth with your lies...

10
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:47,450
Here to say sorry, I presume?

11
00:06:52,780 --> 00:06:55,578
How selfish of you!

12
00:06:55,868 --> 00:07:01,258
I swear you're not really sorry or something... You just want to ease yourself...

13
00:07:01,258 --> 00:07:08,290
Ease the burden that won't let you live in peace or die in peace...

14
00:07:08,290 --> 00:07:13,914
By somehow 'earning' my forgiveness.

15
00:07:14,820 --> 00:07:21,850
All I see is a selfish man, veiled behind regret, seeking to achieve another one of his ends.

16
00:07:22,970 --> 00:07:25,988
That's true too...

17
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:32,348
But there's one more thing...

18
00:07:33,710 --> 00:07:40,547
Something that I value more than my regret or easing the burden of my sin...

19
00:07:40,547 --> 00:07:45,998
I loved you --
-Enough... Just... Shut up...

20
00:07:48,828 --> 00:07:54,878
Love has been helpless for ages...

21
00:07:54,878 --> 00:07:58,010
Don't insult it anymore.

22
00:07:58,010 --> 00:08:05,307
The walls have ears... So stop it before they two-time the ground beneath them and crumble.

23
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:11,688
I'll answer everything you said...

24
00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:18,370
I loved you too...

25
00:08:20,197 --> 00:08:24,558
You were my first and last love...

26
00:08:24,558 --> 00:08:27,650
Because I gave you...

27
00:08:27,650 --> 00:08:30,437
Everything...

28
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:40,142
But now... I hate you...

29
00:08:40,142 --> 00:08:43,637
As purely as I loved you.

30
00:08:43,637 --> 00:08:50,270
Because there's no truer hate than what follows true love...

31
00:08:50,270 --> 00:08:55,700
Forgiveness is too valuable...

32
00:08:55,700 --> 00:09:00,340
It's all I've got left...

33
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:04,668
So don't even think I'm gonna forgive you...

34
00:09:06,337 --> 00:09:08,897
Big words...

35
00:09:08,897 --> 00:09:13,970
When you've been betrayed, shaken... But somehow take it all in...

36
00:09:13,970 --> 00:09:18,941
18 years starts to feel like 80...

37
00:09:28,680 --> 00:09:32,912
May I look at you one last time?
-No!

38
00:09:37,890 --> 00:09:40,030
Go!

39
00:09:40,030 --> 00:09:44,440
Don't even leave your filthy footprints here!

40
00:09:57,070 --> 00:10:03,816
I was so scared... He threatened to kill me... Told me there's a lion and all... Believe me!

41
00:10:03,816 --> 00:10:08,389
Any idea where he could've taken her?
-To the estate.

42
00:10:12,686 --> 00:10:16,236
What've I told him...

43
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:23,180
'Adam <3'

44
00:11:13,470 --> 00:11:16,950
The Reverend's here!

45
00:11:16,950 --> 00:11:21,708
Just say 'I will'...

46
00:11:21,708 --> 00:11:28,098
And many congratulations will reverb in this room...

47
00:11:31,820 --> 00:11:34,760
Refuse...

48
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:38,458
And gunfire will reverb here.

49
00:11:43,820 --> 00:11:46,557
Bring the Reverend here!

50
00:12:09,740 --> 00:12:21,250
... follow the path of Marriage, to love and honour each other for as long as you both shall live?

51
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:30,110
In this life and the next... I'll love and honour no one but my Adam!

52
00:12:31,410 --> 00:12:33,998
What d'you think you're doing?

53
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:06,459
Sort it out between yourselves before calling me, Mr Malik.

54
00:13:06,459 --> 00:13:08,770
Get out!

55
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:23,080
Lemme tell you...

56
00:13:35,090 --> 00:13:37,670
Don't even think about it!

57
00:13:48,450 --> 00:13:54,497
I'll kill myself than let your sinful hands touch me! Back off!

58
00:13:59,830 --> 00:14:01,640
Guddi!

59
00:14:02,710 --> 00:14:04,677
Guddi...

60
00:14:52,030 --> 00:14:53,650
Going somewhere?

61
00:14:53,650 --> 00:14:56,958
Yeah. Just pray for me, okay?

62
00:14:56,958 --> 00:14:58,619
Breakfast?

63
00:14:58,619 --> 00:15:01,228
No, thanks.

64
00:15:01,228 --> 00:15:03,959
Just... Pray for me.

65
00:15:11,020 --> 00:15:12,859
Guddi!

66
00:15:12,859 --> 00:15:16,719
Almost at the hospital... You'll be fine!

67
00:15:16,719 --> 00:15:21,540
The doctors will save you... I pray you live long! Guddi!

68
00:15:21,540 --> 00:15:24,948
You'll be fine... Guddi...

69
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,370
Guddi!

70
00:15:28,370 --> 00:15:30,308
Guddi...

71
00:16:02,890 --> 00:16:06,607
M'boy... Hush...

72
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:22,158
Yeah?

73
00:16:23,070 --> 00:16:25,640
Does Mehek live here?

74
00:16:27,900 --> 00:16:31,616
What do I tell her?

75
00:16:32,150 --> 00:16:36,807
Tell her someone's dying to see her.

76
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:39,878
Okay...

77
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:44,330
You can't be --

78
00:16:44,330 --> 00:16:47,977
S -- Shahmir's Dad?

79
00:16:52,860 --> 00:16:56,618
Shahmir... Lovely name...

80
00:16:59,070 --> 00:17:01,318
Come in!

81
00:17:32,850 --> 00:17:40,097
Doctor... How's she? Please... Tell me everything... She'll be fine, right?

82
00:17:40,097 --> 00:17:47,101
She needs blood... O-. You wouldn't happen to know --
-I'm O-, doctor!

83
00:17:47,101 --> 00:17:54,337
Give her every last drop of blood within me... But I pray you... Save her...

84
00:17:54,337 --> 00:17:56,127
Okay...

85
00:17:56,127 --> 00:17:59,118
Nurse! Come here!

86
00:18:00,790 --> 00:18:06,999
Take him to the lab and check his blood group.
-Okay.
-Which way?

87
00:18:12,750 --> 00:18:16,040
In the Lord's name...

88
00:18:16,040 --> 00:18:16,870
In the Lord's name...
-Mehek!

89
00:18:16,870 --> 00:18:18,180
Mehek!

90
00:18:18,180 --> 00:18:21,840
What happened?
-It's -- Shahmir's Dad! He's here!

91
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:26,038
What?
-Yeah... Shahmir's Dad...

92
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:34,750
Shayan...

93
00:18:35,750 --> 00:18:37,718
C'mon!

94
00:18:39,090 --> 00:18:40,800
Quickly...

95
00:20:29,340 --> 00:20:32,640
What happened? Why'd you stop here?

96
00:20:34,280 --> 00:20:39,370
You sure it's him? Shayan...

97
00:20:42,230 --> 00:20:49,899
I've waited so long... I can't believe it...

98
00:20:49,899 --> 00:20:58,089
I've started seeing things... Hearing things... That made me come here like this... Only to find no one...

99
00:20:59,979 --> 00:21:02,970
My heart is weak...

100
00:21:05,350 --> 00:21:11,343
If he isn't here... My heart may not survive the pain...

101
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:13,657
I'd die...

102
00:21:13,657 --> 00:21:15,617
No, Mehek...

103
00:21:15,617 --> 00:21:18,600
I swear by Shahmir...

104
00:21:55,950 --> 00:21:57,298
How are you?

105
00:21:57,298 --> 00:22:03,429
I'm fine but... How's she? She'll be fine, won't she?
-Let's hope...

