♪ <i>Fallen so far</i> ♪

116
00:23:24,611 --> 00:23:27,413
♪ <i>By the Lord, I claim</i> ♪

117
00:23:27,413 --> 00:23:30,188
♪ <i>I'll never be the same...</i> ♪

118
00:23:30,188 --> 00:23:37,032
♪ <i>My resolve faded as an aching wound took over</i> ♪

119
00:23:37,032 --> 00:23:40,158
♪ <i>Yea, took over...</i> ♪

120
00:23:42,209 --> 00:23:45,014
♪ <i>You were distant though so near</i> ♪

121
00:23:45,014 --> 00:23:47,784
♪ <i>You're distant yet so dear</i> ♪

122
00:23:47,784 --> 00:23:50,564
♪ <i>You etched your name on my heart, right here</i> ♪

123
00:23:50,564 --> 00:23:53,464
♪ <i>You forgot me, yet you're dear...</i> ♪

124
00:23:58,420 --> 00:24:01,069
Pull me up...

125
00:24:02,050 --> 00:24:04,409
Curse me...

126
00:24:07,680 --> 00:24:11,208
Grab my collar and ask me...

127
00:24:14,740 --> 00:24:18,078
Slap me if you want too...

128
00:24:21,500 --> 00:24:25,600
But please... Don't torment me with this silence...

129
00:24:28,520 --> 00:24:33,370
All of that is done...

130
00:24:33,370 --> 00:24:37,678
To those who matter...

131
00:24:37,678 --> 00:24:42,150
Your love makes you do it...

132
00:24:42,150 --> 00:24:46,113
But... You don't matter to me anymore...

133
00:24:46,113 --> 00:24:51,484
Your betrayal smothered my love.

134
00:24:51,484 --> 00:24:56,475
I or my son don't care about you one bit!

135
00:24:57,160 --> 00:25:03,080
You've wronged us both...

136
00:25:03,080 --> 00:25:06,369
And this is your sentence...

137
00:25:06,369 --> 00:25:09,240
Go. Just go!

138
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:13,438
I swear it's not my fault!

139
00:25:13,843 --> 00:25:19,480
Fate has been unkind...

140
00:25:19,480 --> 00:25:21,248
Too unkind...

141
00:25:21,248 --> 00:25:23,438
Almost...

142
00:25:23,438 --> 00:25:26,958
Like a mortal enemy...

143
00:25:30,780 --> 00:25:39,219
Every moment I've lived without you, I've prayed to get to see you again...

144
00:25:41,750 --> 00:25:49,120
Begged the declining dusk, the endless night, and the blinding day...

145
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:52,717
To have...

146
00:25:52,717 --> 00:25:56,737
To have just an ounce of mercy...

147
00:25:58,078 --> 00:26:01,138
It's not my fault...

148
00:26:01,600 --> 00:26:05,660
But fate has been unkind... To both of us...

149
00:26:05,660 --> 00:26:14,980
Then... Tell me... Give me reason to believe you're innocent! Tell me what happened!

150
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:23,070
My loyalty warns me against listening to a cheat like you...

151
00:26:23,070 --> 00:26:28,944
Reminding, cautioning, screaming, and begging me not to fall for your lies again...

152
00:26:42,540 --> 00:26:44,300
Alright...

153
00:27:40,240 --> 00:27:45,000
I've never asked for anything in life...

154
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:48,361
Didn't know... Didn't want to know how...

155
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:54,000
You're the first thing I'm asking for, Guddi...

156
00:28:08,500 --> 00:28:12,930
I've lost a lot in life...

157
00:28:12,930 --> 00:28:15,157
A lot...

158
00:28:17,850 --> 00:28:20,228
But you...

159
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:40,439
You're the first reward that's truly and sincerely mine... Let me reap it, mate...

160
00:28:41,728 --> 00:28:44,141
You're fine now, Guddi...

161
00:28:44,141 --> 00:28:47,682
So get up, byt. C'mon...

162
00:29:03,930 --> 00:29:05,978
How's she, Doctor?

163
00:29:05,978 --> 00:29:10,451
She's safe now. She'll come to any moment.

164
00:29:12,240 --> 00:29:15,044
Thank you, my Lord...

165
00:29:15,390 --> 00:29:17,267
Thank You...

166
00:29:17,267 --> 00:29:19,310
Doctor...

167
00:29:19,310 --> 00:29:23,160
If she's fine now, could I go? Got something to do...

168
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:25,257
Of course.

169
00:29:25,257 --> 00:29:27,418
You may go.

170
00:29:27,418 --> 00:29:29,924
Thank you.
-Okay.

171
00:29:57,370 --> 00:30:04,120
I beg you... And my son...

172
00:30:04,120 --> 00:30:08,767
To forgive me... For giving in...

173
00:30:08,767 --> 00:30:13,477
For not being there for you... When you needed me the most...

174
00:30:15,650 --> 00:30:25,960
My heart wants to believe everything you've said... It believes every word you've said...

175
00:30:25,960 --> 00:30:31,397
But my mind warns me against it... Against falling for it again...

176
00:30:31,397 --> 00:30:35,180
How do I pay a deaf ear to my mind?

177
00:30:35,180 --> 00:30:39,130
It's suffered a lot...

178
00:30:39,130 --> 00:30:41,977
Suffered a lot...

179
00:30:44,700 --> 00:30:48,860
If you don't believe me... Ask Adam.

180
00:30:49,330 --> 00:30:52,997
He got me out of that place.

181
00:30:53,690 --> 00:30:55,748
What?

182
00:30:58,360 --> 00:31:01,960
A -- Adam got you out?

183
00:31:32,390 --> 00:31:35,398
Don't worry... Daddy's here...

184
00:31:36,990 --> 00:31:39,057
Shahmir...

185
00:32:07,740 --> 00:32:09,527
Enough...

186
00:32:10,870 --> 00:32:17,169
I'm tired of living a suffocating lie...

187
00:32:17,169 --> 00:32:20,191
I've got to tell Grandpa everything...

188
00:32:20,191 --> 00:32:22,640
Gotta tell him...

189
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:25,910
Everything...

190
00:32:38,200 --> 00:32:40,161
Yeah, Kheru?

191
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:43,008
No one here, Adam...

192
00:32:43,008 --> 00:32:46,319
No one? Where'd he go?

193
00:32:46,790 --> 00:32:49,280
Malik flippin' Jr!

194
00:33:38,210 --> 00:33:42,370
Mehek... I made a big mistake...

195
00:33:42,370 --> 00:33:44,397
What happened?

196
00:34:04,810 --> 00:34:06,268
Malik Jr!

197
00:34:06,268 --> 00:34:08,360
Where's he?

198
00:34:08,360 --> 00:34:10,960
Enough, Mehek...

199
00:34:10,960 --> 00:34:12,710
Enough...

200
00:34:12,710 --> 00:34:18,000
Adam won't 'yes' you this time. Where's Malik Jr?

